"fn\">V</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hcomm</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i </span><span class=\"fn\">j</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>) (<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\">R</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">j</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Commute/Defs.html#Commute\">Commute</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Basis/Defs.html#Module.Basis.coord\">coord</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Transvection.html#LinearMap.transvection\">transvection</a></span> (<span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span> <span class=\"fn\">j</span></span>))</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Subring/Basic.html#Subring.center\">Subring.center</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A linear endomorphism of a free module of rank at least 2\nthat commutes with transvections consists of homotheties with central ratio. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Center.html#LinearMap.commute_transvections_iff_of_basis","kind":"theorem","line":58,"name":"LinearMap.commute_transvections_iff_of_basis","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/LinearAlgebr